title: ninkyou_tensei
body: [b]Yakuza Reincarnation[/b], also known as [i]Ninkyō Tensei –Isekai no Yakuza Hime–[/i] (任侠転生 –異世界のヤクザ姫–) is a manga series written by Takeshi Natsuhara and illustrated by [[Miyashita Hiroki]]. It is a [[genderswap]] [[isekai]] manga about an old [[yakuza]] man who dies and wakes up in another world in the body of a young princess, retaining his back tattoo and strength, and rebuilds the princess' territory with yakuza chivalry.

title: isuzu_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
[[Isuzu_(kancolle)|]]'s second remodel.

The first member of the Nagara-class to have received a second remodel, her new uniform features a white collar and a radar headband while she gained several chest sizes (in part due to the artist improving). She now holds two guns, a bullpup-like Twin 12.7 cm AA gun and a SMG-like Triple 25mm AA gun holding a depth charge. This came with much stronger AA and ASW stats but a short attack range if she isn't given a surface gun.

title: eve_(stellar_blade)
body:
Main character from [[Stellar Blade]]. Her name is stylized as "EVE".

A commando of the 7th Airborne Division of the Space Colony. Eve was sent to Earth in a combat mission against Earthlings, but her entire unit was wiped out. She was saved by [[Adam (Stellar Blade)|]], and began her journey to adapt and survive in her new home.

EVE is a [[tall female|tall woman]] with a [[long legs]], [[medium breasts|medium]] to [[large breasts]] (depending on costume she's wearing), [[brown eyes]] and [[black hair]]. Her default hairstyle is a [[very long hair|very long]] [[ponytail]] with [[blunt bangs|blunt]] [[medium bangs]], though the player can change it in the options menu. She has various small [[mole]]s across her body and face. Her default outfit is a [[Planet Diving Suit (7th) (Stellar Blade)|]]. She also wears different types of heels depending on the outfit the player chooses. Her [[sword]] [[Blood Edge (Stellar Blade)|]] folds up and functions as a [[hairclip]] for her ponytail when not in use.

h4. Appearance

* !post #8640908: [[Planet Diving Suit (7th) (Stellar Blade)|]]
* !post #9431156: [[Skin suit (Stellar Blade)|]]

h4. External links

* "Stellar Blade Wiki: EVE":https://stellarblade.fandom.com/wiki/EVE

title: skin_suit_(stellar_blade)
body:
A [[bodysuit]] outfit for [[eve_(stellar_blade)|Eve]] in [[Stellar Blade]].

As its name suggests, it is a skin-colored bodysuit that [[revealing clothes|exposes large amount of skin of the wearer]], which combined with the color of the suit itself (with the "skin" part of the suit suggestively covering Eve's breasts and [[ass]]) can make Eve appears as if she was naked.

Not recommended for new players as it greatly increases the damage Eve takes, making the game considerably more difficult.

h5. In-game description:
[i]"Changes the appearance of Eve. Skin suits are outfits specifically crafted by Mother Sphere. It covers the body of Airborn Squad Member and deploys on its own, or expands and contracts depending on the situation. In other words, it's like a living skin. (Shield is disabled when you put on this Skin Suit.)"[/i]

h5. Appearance
* !post #9431156

title: spider-verse_(comics)
body:
A series of crossover [[Spider-Man (series)|]] comics featuring various Spider-heroes from various universes fighting an interdimensional threat. The series debuted with a run from 2014 to 2015, and has since had several sequels.

The concept of a multiversal Spider-Man crossover was very well received, and would go onto to inspire the award winning film [[Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse]] and its sequels.

This tag is for posts that feature depictions of characters based on their comic incarnations and [[official art]] from the comics.

h4. Spider-Verse Runs
* Spider-Verse (2014-2015)
* Secret Wars (2015)
* Spider-Geddon (2018)
* End of the Spider-Verse (2022-2023)

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Spider-Verse":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spider-Verse

title: wattson_(apex_legends)
body:
Wattson is a playable Legend in [[Apex Legends]], added to the game in season 2.

Wattson has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her most distinctive feature is a [[burn scar]] on her left cheek in the shape of a [[Lichtenberg figure]]. Her default costume consists of a [[hooded bodysuit|hooded]] [[blue bodysuit|blue]] [[ribbed bodysuit]] worn under a [[white bodysuit]] with [[cable]]s and an [[orange jacket|orange]] [[hooded jacket]] with a [[lightning bolt symbol]] on the upper arm. She also wears [[blue gloves]] and [[white shoes|white]] [[sneakers]].

She is often pictured wielding an [[L-STAR]], as the weapon was added to the game at the same time as her, and her heirloom weapon is the [[Energy Reader (apex legends)|]]. She has a pet [[cat]] named [[Nikola (apex legends)|]], and is notably fond of [[Nessie (respawn)|]] - to the point that she's credited as the person responsible for the plushies hidden around the various maps.

Wattson is voiced by "Justine Huxley":[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0404722/] in English and [[Kondou Yui]] in Japanese.

title: pillowdear_(old_design)
body:
The original costume of the [[indie virtual youtuber|Indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] [[PillowDear]], used in her early streams before debuting her Live2D model. It was designed and drawn by Pillow herself.

This original costume featured a [[cable knit]], [[sleeveless]] [[sweater]] similar to her [[pillowdear (1st costume)|current Live2D default]]. The main difference was that her old sweater did not feature a [[cleavage cutout]] in the shape of a heart, nor did it have an [[backless outfit|exposed back]]. Other differences include [[mismatched socks]] that were white and black, a [[red jacket]] rather than a red blanket, long [[red nails]], no [[arrows]] on her person, and a black [[bracelet]] worn on her left arm.

title: g11_(fluffy_dumptruck)_(girls'_frontline)
body:
[[G11 (girls' frontline)|]]'s ninth skin from [[Girls' Frontline]], as part of the 'Childhood Case Files' skin collection from 2023.

Unique to G11 in this skin collection, she has two forms - [[aged down]] in her undamaged art, and [[aged up]] in her damaged art. Both forms possess [[mouse ears]].

When [b]aged down[/b], she wears a [[short sleeves|short]] [[single sleeve]]ed [[white shirt]] [[short over long sleeves|over]] a [[long sleeves|long sleeved]] [[black shirt]] - wherein the left sleeve of the black shirt is [[stitches|stitched]] into the sleeveless portion of the white shirt, [[no pants]], [[white shoes|white]] [[sneakers]] with [[black socks]], and a [[red headband]].

When [b]aged up[/b], she wears the same white shirt and jacket - except [[torn clothes|torn]] and only the left sleeve is barely intact, [[white pants]], [[mismatched footwear|mismatched]] [[slippers]], and the same [[red headband]].

title: hololive_idol_uniform_(bright)
body:
The [[official alternate costume|official]] [[idol clothes]] worn by [[hololive]] members for live events and in certain [[promotional art|promotional artworks]] between 2023 and 2025, created for the 2023 4th hololive Festival "Our Bright Parade". The base version of the outfit was designed by [[Amagai Tarou]], while [[Mika Pikazo]] designed a variation for the overseas talents.

Just like with the original idol uniform version and the hololive summer swimsuit, for special events it's not uncommon for the top to be replaced with a [[t-shirt]] featuring the [[logo]] of the event instead.

h4. Versions

h6. hololive Japan version

It consists of a [[white jacket|white]] [[short-sleeved jacket]] with [[puffy short sleeves]], a color-coded [[bowtie]], a [[white shirt]], a blue [[underbust]] [[corset]], a color-coded [[sash]] with a [[waist bow|bow]] running from the waist to the hip, a [[layered skirt|layered]] [[overskirt]] consisting of a and [[white skirt]] and a [[two-sided skirt|two-sided]] layer with [[blue skirt|blue]] on the outside and a color-coded inner layer and a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow|back]][[bow skirt|bow]], worn over either a [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[blue skirt|blue]] [[miniskirt]] or a pair of [[blue shorts]] with a [[thigh strap]], [[blue socks|blue]] [[bobby socks]] and [[high heel boots|high-heel]] [[ankle boots]] with [[footwear bow]]s and [[colored shoe soles|color-coded soles]] 

h6. [[hololive English]] version

It consists of a white [[double-breasted]] [[crop top]] with [[uneven sleeves]],  a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[black skirt|black]] and [[white skirt|white]] [[half-skirt]] with [[crinoline]] worn over a [[black skirt|black]] [[plaid skirt]] with multiple [[bow]]s attached, a black [[thigh strap]], a [[white pantyhose|white]] [[single leg pantyhose]] with a sparkle [[print pantyhose|print]] and [[mismatched footwear]] consisting of a [[white boots|white]] [[single boot]] on one foot and a color-coded [[strappy heels|strappy heel]] on the other

h6. [[hololive Indonesia]] version

The holoID version replaces the single-piece top with a color-coded [[cropped shirt]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] and [[short over long sleeves]] on one side, the bottom is a color-coded [[overskirt]] worn over either [[multicolored shorts]] with [[thigh strap]]s or a color-coded [[half-skirt]] worn over a [[frilled skirt]], [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]] [[socks]] and [[white shoes|white]] [[sneakers]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #6019569: Reference sheet (hololive Indonesia)

* [[hololive idol uniform (Color Rise)]]

title: char_aznable
body:
The main antagonist of [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] and the eponymous [[Char's Counterattack]], a supporting character in [[zeta gundam|Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]] and eternal rival and foe of [[Amuro Ray]]. Also appears in [[Gundam GQuuuuuux]].

[b]Char Aznable[/b], also known as [b]The Red Comet[/b] by the [[Earth Federation Space Forces]] [spoilers](as he was able to destroy 5 Federation battleships with a simple red colored [[Zaku II]] in quick succession during the "Battle of Loum":https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Battle_of_Loum)[/spoilers]), is originally a blonde-haired [[Zeon]] ace pilot of the [[Zaku II S Char Custom|MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type]], [[z'gok char custom|Z'Gok]], [[gelgoog s char custom|Gelgoog]], [[Zeong|MSN-02 Zeong]], [[AEUG]] [[Rick Dias]], [[Gundam Mk II]], [[Zero Shiki (gundam)|]], [[Hyaku Shiki|MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki]] and the [[Neo Zeon]] [[Char's Dijeh]], [[Dijeh Traversia]], [[Geara Doga Psycommu Test Type]] and the [[Prototype Sazabi]]/[[Sazabi|MSN-04 Sazabi]]/[[nightingale (gundam)|MSN-04II Nightingale]]. 

He is usually depicted with some sort of eyewear or headwear (usually [[sunglasses]] or his trademark [[helmet]]), concealing his eyes.

[spoilers]His real name is [b][[Casval Rem Deikun]][/b] and he has [[blue eyes]]. He stole the identity of [[char aznable (real)|the real Char Aznable]]  (who is mostly identical to him except his brown eyes) to avoid being killed by [[Kycilia Zabi]] as a part of her plan to purge the Deikun family, and as such he chose to conceal his eyes to hide his real identity. He is the actual brother of [[Sayla Mass]]/[[Artesia Som Deikun]] and the true heir to Zeon.[/spoilers]

Char's name was inspired by the real life Franco-Armenian singer and actor "Charles Aznavour":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Aznavour. In [[Japan]] Char is as well known and popular as iconic characters [[Darth Vader]] and [[spock|Mr. Spock]] are in the West. 

He is voiced by [[Ikeda Shuuichi]].

title: ishtar_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character from [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War]].

The inheritor to the Mjölnir tome and a recurring antagonist, her mind is riddled with doubt between choosing the side of justice and fighting for her dearly beloved [[Julius (Fire Emblem)|]]. [spoiler]Choosing the latter of those options, she ends up confronting [[Seliph (Fire Emblem)|]] several times throughout the adventure, all the while secretly helping [[Arvis (fire emblem)|]] combat the Child Hunts initiated by Julius in spite of her love for the latter. Ishtar ultimately meets her demise near Belhalla, falling in battle to the liberation army in a last stand.[/spoiler]

Class: [b]Sage[/b]
Holy Blood: Thrud [b](Major)[/b]

title: stylet
body:
Stiletto is a character from [[kotobukiya|Kotobukiya’s]] model kit series [[Frame Arms Girl]].

She is the anthropomorphized version of the Frame Arms “Stiletto” mecha, reimagined as a blue-haired, armored girl with futuristic design elements. 

Stiletto features short [[blue hair]] with distinctive [[twintails|twin-tail]] attachments, light [[blue eyes]], and a stylish, [[mecha musume|mechanical bodysuit]]. 

Her equipment is inspired by aircraft weaponry, including [[missile]]s, a [[gatling gun]], and [[knife|knives]]. 

Known for her tsundere and competitive personality, Stiletto often sees [[Gourai]] as her rival but also cares deeply for her friends. 

In the anime adaptation, she is voiced by [[Ogura Yui]].

title: gourai
body:

She is the anthropomorphized version of the original [[Gourai (frame arms)|]] mecha, depicted as a brown-haired girl with a [[bob cut]] and [[blue eyes]].

Her appearance features heavy [[mecha musume]]-style [[armor]], a [[helmet]], and a [[bodysuit]]. 

She is equipped mainly with weapons inspired by [[tank]]s and ground combat vehicles, such as [[mechanical arms]], a [[shield]], and a [[cannon]].

Gourai is known for her honest, innocent personality and her ability to learn and grow quickly. 

She cares deeply for her friends. In the anime, she is voiced by [[Narumi Kaho]].

title: ultra_beam
body:
A signature move from the [[Ultra Series]] franchise. All Ultramen can perform an Ultra Beam, but the execution and pose may differ between them. An Ultra Beam is most commonly performed by forming a cross-shape or an L-shape with your arms and firing a beam from your upright arm.

It is believed that the reason why some Ultra Beams have a cross-shape position is due to the fact that [[Tsuburaya Eiji]], the creator of the Ultra Series, converted to Roman Catholicism, and he borrowed Christian elements to be used as ideas for his works.

h4. External links

* Ultraman Wiki: "Ultra Beam":[https://ultra.fandom.com/wiki/Ultra_Beam]

title: nontraditional_miko
body:
A modernized or adapted [[miko]] outfit. [[Hakurei Reimu]]'s and [[Yae Miko]]'s outfits are prime examples of this.

Common features of nontraditional miko outfits include:

* [[Hakama short skirt]]s – shortened to resemble modern short skirts, especially [[pleated skirt|pleated skirts]]
* [[Sleeveless]] [[kimono]] tops,  often with [[detached sleeves]]
* [[Thighhighs]] – especially white [[tabi]] ones with [[ribbon-trimmed_legwear|ribbon trims]]
* High-heeled ([[wedge heels|wedge]] or [[platform heels|platform-heeled]]) [[sandals]], often worn with above thighhighs
* Generally designs with elements taken from modern fashions like [[lolita_fashion|lolita]], [[school uniform|school uniforms]], etc.

Nontraditional miko outfits should not be tagged [[miko]], as that tag is for traditional miko outfits.

h4. See also

* [[Adapted uniform]]
* [[Japanese clothes]]

title: miko
body:
Shrine maidens in [[Shinto]] [[shrine|shrines]] (not the same rank as priests, closer to altar boys). They sweep the shrine, do ceremonial dances, perform music, flank the priest at prayers, freshen the offerings, operate the fortune telling lottery ([[omikuji]]), sell votive tablets ([[ema]]), and in most modern shrines run the knickknack and good luck charms shop. Historically, they used to be mediums and oracles, alongside the male [[Geki]]. They are often depicted wielding [[gohei]].

This tag is for pictures where at least one character is wearing the traditional outfit of a miko: a [[hakama skirt]] (almost always entirely red) and white [[kosode]].

Conversely, do not use this tag if the character in question is employed as a shrine maiden but does not wear the traditional outfit of a miko described above. Tag them as [[nontraditional miko]] instead. [[Hakurei Reimu]] and [[Yae Miko]] are prominent examples of this.

h4. Clothings

title: crossover
body:
A crossover is when two or more characters from unrelated copyrights are shown together in one scene. 

Crossover should not be confused with [[parody]]. A parody implies mimicking a scene or dialogue from another series, with the intention of being humorous.

One character [[cosplay|cosplaying]] as a character from another series does not normally qualify as a crossover.

Use [[songover]] for crossovers between multiple songs or other musical compositions, seen commonly with [[Vocaloid]] songs.

h4. See also

* [[company connection]]
* [[creator connection]]
* [[in-franchise crossover]]
* [[multiple crossover]]
* [[parody]]

They were working for the company [i][[Atelier Kaguya]][/i], a Japanese eroge maker. They mainly draw illustrations for the games of "Team Heartbeat", a sub-division of the company A-Kaguya, and has been doing so since 2003. They're now working for Astronauts, another adult game brand.

title: hypnosis_mic:_dream_rap_battle
body:
A mobile RPG based off the [[Hypnosis Mic]] franchise.

The player takes on the role of an intern at a company that is developing a [[virtual reality]] metaverse called MIRA. During an event meant to be a rap battle exhibition to showcase the MCs (or rappers) who had progressed past the second Division Rap Battle, a critical error occurs with the AI governing the metaverse which results in every user that had been logged in being incapable of logging out, save for the developers and MCs who manage to log out with debug mode. This effectively leaves anyone who had joined to view the exhibition trapped in the metaverse.

The game introduces AI [[dark persona]]s of the [[Hypnosis Mic|18 Division Rap Battle participants]]. These AI personas are referred to as "ghosts" and have primarily monochrome appearances with [[grey skin]] and [[white hair]] (with the exception of [[Aohitsugi Samatoki]]'s ghost who is given [[black hair]] due to Samatoki himself already having white hair). The only colors in their appearances are their glowing eyes which remain the same as their human counterparts and spot coloring in their clothing that is their respective division's motif color (Red for Buster Bros!!!, Blue for Mad Trigger Crew, etc.)

The story is original to the game and is not considered a part of the mainline Hypnosis Mic canon.

h4. See also

* [[Hypnosis Mic]]
* [[Hypnosis Mic: Alternative Rap Battle]]
* [[Hypnosis Mic: Rule The Stage]]
* [[Hypnosis Mic: Rhyme Anima]]

title: girly_boy
body:
A boy who acts recognizably feminine but can still be easily identified as male. "Onee" type boys will often be of this demographic, owing to girlish speech patterns or hobbies.
In general, the difference between this tag and [[trap]] is whether you can tell that the character is male without looking at the genitals. If you can, they're [[girly boy]], otherwise they're a [[trap]].

Most characters of this type will have an interest in topics typically associated with femininity (dandy-style fashion, beauty, cute things, etc.) and often are depicted in coquettish poses. They may wear [[high heels]], [[jewelry]], [[makeup]] and/or [[nail polish]]. Common hairstyles may be wavy or flipped.

Not to be confused with [[trap]] (sometimes referred to as "femboys" in English), which is a boy whose [i]physical appearance[/i] is feminine regardless of his personality. Also not to be confused with the term and archetype of "okama", though characters of either type can have girly boy traits. [[Crossdressing]] does not automatically make a character a "girly boy" either. 

h4. Examples

* !post #2483256
* !post #6441656
* !post #5202625  

h4. Notable characters

* [[Scandinavia Peperoncino]] from [[Fate/Grand Order]]
* [[britney_(taisou_samurai)|Britney]] from [[Taiso Samurai]]
* [[Narukami Arashi]] from [[Ensemble Stars!]] [tn]Arashi identifies as female but is physically male, so from appearance alone she qualifies as a "girly boy"[/tn]

h4. See also
* [[tomboy]] (feminine counterpart)
* [[fabulous]]

title: smegma
body: Often depicted as a cloudy or white substance built up under the [[foreskin]] of a [[penis]]. Significant buildup, colloquially "dick cheese", connotes a foul odor, color, and texture. Regular hygiene of the genitalia (not exclusively male) clears away much of the substance, which otherwise lubricates the affected tissues.

title: vielle
body: The vielleis a European bowed stringed instrument used in the medieval period, similar to a modern violin but with a somewhat longer and deeper body, three to five gut strings, and a leaf-shaped pegbox with frontal tuning pegs, sometimes with a figure-8 shaped body.

title: sigurd_(fire_emblem)
body:
Sigurd (romanized as [b]Siglud[/b] in the Japanese version) is the main Lord character of [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War]], the inheritor of the duchy of Chalphy and a full-blooded descendant of Crusader [[Baldr (Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War)|]]. [[Deirdre (Fire Emblem)|]] is his wife, and together, they have a son named [[Seliph (Fire Emblem)|]].

As a full-blooded descendant of Crusader Baldo, Sigurd wields the holy sword [[Tyrfing (Fire Emblem)|]], which is later passed down to his son Seliph.

[spoilers]Sigurd is ultimately killed by [[Arvis (Fire Emblem)|]] at the end of the First Generation, and his son Seliph succeeds him for the Second Generation.[/spoilers]

Holy Blood: [b][[Baldr (Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War)|]][/b] (major)

body:

title: blackwargreymon
body:
Ultimate-level Dragon Man [[Digimon (creature)|]]. A Virus-attribute variant of [[Wargreymon|War Greymon]] feared as the "Jet-black Dragon Warrior", this subspecies features [[black scales]] and [[black armor]], unlike its Vaccine-attribute counterpart. Despite this mysterious change in attribute and disposition, it still fights for the sake of its own brand of 'justice', and it despises cowardice and foul play. For that reason, it refuses to associate itself with vulgar Digimon, even if those happen to be Virus Digimon. Also, its [[shield|Brave Shield]] does not feature the Crest of Courage.

Black War Greymon has [[yellow eyes]], much like its prior forms, and [[blonde hair]].

[u]Common evolutionary throughline[/u]
[[Botamon]] -> [[Koromon]] -> [[Agumon (Black)]] -> [[Greymon (Blue)]] -> [[Metalgreymon (Virus)|Metal Greymon (Virus)]] -> [b]Black War Greymon[/b]
* Black War Greymon can evolve upon exposure to the [[Blackwargreymon X-Antibody|X-Antibody]].
* [[Gaioumon]] is a related X-Antibody Greymon-species Digimon, being a Dragon Man Digimon with a few similar traits.
* It has been depicted as Jogress Evolving with [[Metalgarurumon (Black)|Metal Garurumon (Black)]] into [[Omegamon Zwart]].
other_names: ブラックウォーグレイモン

title: metalgreymon_(virus)
body:
Perfect-level Cyborg [[Digimon (creature)|]]. A Virus-attribute version of [[Metalgreymon|Metal Greymon]], this subspecies features [[blue scales]] all around with no striping. Its process of mechanization has left its [[claws]] and [[talons]] discolored in a similar blue as its scales, and its [[yellow eyes]] feature [[slit pupils]], resulting in a more aggressive and feral look than its Vaccine-attribute cousin. Its [[horns]] have also assumed the same silver color as the [[helmet]] on its head.

[u]Common evolutionary throughline[/u]
[[Botamon]] -> [[Koromon]] -> [[Agumon (Black)]] -> [[Greymon (Blue)]] -> [b]Metal Greymon (Virus)[/b] -> [[Blackwargreymon|Black War Greymon]]
* Metal Greymon (Virus) can evolve upon exposure to the [[Metalgreymon (Virus) X-Antibody|X-Antibody]].
* In [[Digimon Adventure 02]], when the [[Digimon Kaiser]] forcibly makes [[Agumon]] Super-Evolve with a Dark Spiral, his Metal Greymon (Virus) form uniquely features a pale blue coloration with dark blue stripes. This coloration has not been featured elsewhere since.
* This was actually the first known variant of Metal Greymon, having been introduced in 1997; the orange Vaccine Metal Greymon was only introduced in 1999, in [[Digimon Adventure]].
other_names: メタルグレイモン(ウィルス種)
元祖メタルグレイモン

title: greymon_(blue)
body:
Adult-level Dinosaur [[Digimon (creature)|]]. This [[blue scales|blue]] variant of Greymon is a Virus-attribute variant of [[Greymon|the more well-known Vaccine-attribute subspecies]]. It notably features [[yellow eyes]]. This viral Greymon is also more feral and violent in nature than its orange cousin.

[u]Common evolutionary throughline[/u]
[[Botamon]] -> [[Koromon]] -> [[Agumon (Black)]] -> [b]Greymon (Blue)[/b] -> [[Metalgreymon (Virus)|Metal Greymon (Virus)]] -> [[Blackwargreymon|Black War Greymon]]
* Greymon (Blue) can evolve upon exposure to the [[Greymon (Blue) X-Antibody|X-Antibody]].

title: ylgr_(fire_emblem)
body:
Ylgr is a Book II character from [[Fire Emblem Heroes]]. She is the youngest of the Niflese royal siblings. She has the power to communicate with others through her dreams like the rest of her siblings; however, her power is less pronounced than her eldest sisters' and she cannot recall her dreams in great detail when she awakens. Naive and brimming with curiosity, she's eager to explore new horizons.

title: catwoman_(movie)
body: Catwoman is a 2004 American superhero film directed by Pitof and written by John Rogers. It is loosely based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Catwoman]]. The film stars Halle Berry, Benjamin Bratt, Lambert Wilson, Frances Conroy, Alex Borstein, and Sharon Stone. Its plot centers on Patience Phillips, a meek graphic designer, who discovers a conspiracy within the cosmetics company she works for that involves a dangerous product that could cause widespread health problems. After being discovered and murdered by the conspirators, Patience is revived by an Egyptian mau cat that grants her superhuman cat-like abilities, allowing her to become the crime-fighting superheroine Catwoman.

title: dragon_quest_i
body:
The first in the long-running [i][[Dragon Quest]][/i] series of video games.  Although a very simple game by modern standards, it did establish many of the modern tropes of console RPGs.

It was originally released in 1986 for the [[Famicom]], and brought to North America in 1990, though its name was changed to [i]Dragon Warrior[/i] in that market due to a previous copyright on the [i]Dragon Quest[/i] title.  The game has since been ported and enhanced numerous times, with versions being made for the [[Super Famicom]], [[Game Boy Color]], and mobile devices.

title: keaton_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Keaton[/b] (フランネル, [i]Flannel[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Keaton is a Wolfskin, capable of turning into werewolf-like creatures. Living on Mount Garou, a Nohrian mountain range, he is the leader of his pack. While well-dressed and fulfilling a leader function, he is extremely messy and not in the least bit concerned with his appearance. He is most attracted to objects out of everyone in the army.

He is voiced by Jun Osuka in the Japanese version and by Gideon Emery in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wolfskin

title: hrid_(fire_emblem)
body:
Hríd is a Book II character from [[Fire Emblem Heroes]]. He is the first prince of the Ice Kingdom Nifl; He is the older brother of Princesses [[gunnthra (fire emblem)|Gunnthrá]], [[Fjorm (fire emblem)|]] and [[Ylgr (fire emblem)|]], making him the eldest royalty of Nifl. title: shoulder_devil
body:
A type of stock character that is used as a means of depicting a character's moral dilemmas. A shoulder devil is, most commonly, a small [[demon boy]] or [[demon girl]] appearing on a character's shoulder or beside their head to act as temptation and guide them towards the path of evil or mischief. They can be pictured as a smaller version of the character or as another character, usually but not always with added [[demon horns]], [[demon wings]], and a [[demon tail]].

They are almost always accompanied by a [[shoulder angel]] on the character's opposite shoulder. A character can be marked as especially evil or mischievous by having another shoulder devil in the angel's place or by receiving similarly bad advice from both their shoulder angel and their shoulder devil.

title: faye_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character from [[Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia]], also appearing in [[Fire Emblem Heroes]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[brown_hair|brown]] [[twin braids]] with [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon]]s, two notable [[flipped hair|flipped]] portions of her hair, and has [[brown eyes]].  She wears a tattered brown [[corset]]ed [[dress]] with a white [[apron]].

She is a childhood friend of [[Alm (fire emblem)|]]'s, and follows him into battle. As her devotion to Alm (who is already clearly committed to [[Celica (fire emblem)|]]), she is frequently portrayed as [[yandere]] in her affection for Alm, and potentially violently jealous of Celica (although in-game, she gets a passive support with Celica and can be recruited by Celica's side).

Starting as a ("trainee"-type) villager unit, she could obtain many different possible final classes in Shadows of Valentia, from Paladin to Falcon Knight to Saint to Priestess. In spite of this, in Heroes, her only class is as an Archer, which is notably one of the few weapons she [i]couldn't[/i] learn to use.

body:

Their body shape comes to an end just behind the dorsal and anal fins, giving them a "half-fish" appearance. 

The most Famous members of this family is the Ocean Sunfish ([i]Mola Mola[/i]) and the Southern Sunfish ([i]Mola Alexandrini[/i]).

This tag will also apply for freshwater sunfish in the family, Centrarchidae.

title: school_swimsuit
body:
A standard school-issued [[one-piece swimsuit]] usually blue, black, white or grey in color sometimes with the wearer's name written or printed on a white [[name tag]] stitched across the chest. The style has evolved over the years.

The original [[old school swimsuit]] has thicker shoulder straps, vertical seams over torso and a [[school swimsuit flap|flap]] over the groin.

The [[new school swimsuit]] is identical in style to the old school swimsuit except with no flap over the groin.

The [[competition school swimsuit]] has thinner shoulder straps, is unseamed and has no flap over the groin. It is closer in style to the more modern [[competition swimsuit]], but still in the style of a school swimsuit.

The [[nontraditional school swimsuit|non-traditional school swimsuit]] is a swimsuit that has been patterned after a school swimsuit, but is two-piece, frilled, or has other alterations to it that deviate from the norm.


h4. Examples

title: sphere_hair_ornament
body:
A [[hair ornament]] shaped like an orb. This is meant for a large orb or more exotic designs that incorporate multiple spheres and/or other designs.

If you see a couple of small spheres attached to an elastic, use [[hair bobbles]] instead. If the hair ornament(s) are meant to resemble a planet, use [[planet hair ornament]] instead. For beads that are strung together and worn as an ornament, use [[hair beads]] instead. This tag is intended for more outlandish designs or distinctly large spheres.

title: songstress_(final_fantasy)
body: A class introduced in [[Final Fantasy X-2]], which is the game’s more modernized version of the Bard class in previous titles. [[Yuna (ff10)|]] and [[Lenne (ff10)|]] wear the same Songstress outfit, while [[Rikku (ff10)|]] and [[Paine (ff10)|]] have their own designs.

title: kamio_akira
body:
A [[Tennis no Ouji-sama]] character. He is the vice-captain of Fudomine Junior High School's boys' tennis team. He is one of the team's aces alongside his doubles partner and long-time friend, [[Ibu Shinji]].

Though he is overall a good-natured person, he has a belligerent streak that can be seen in his tendency to provoke his opponents prior to matches and his quick response to other people's provocations. He has a strong desire to improve himself and hates to lose. He's been shown to be extremely jealous of boys who are close to his crush, [[Tachibana An]].

title: red_chain_(pokemon)
body:
An item in the [[pokemon|Pokémon]] series. It is a [[chain]] created from [[crystal]]s extracted from the three lake guardians: [[Uxie]], [[Mesprit]], and [[Azelf]].

It is most notably used by [[Cyrus (pokemon)|]] in an attempt to summon and control [[Dialga]] and/or [[Palkia]].

h4. Official art
* "Bulbapedia":https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Chain

title: star_wars:_the_high_republic
body:
A multimedia subseries of the [[Star Wars]] franchise, first released in 2021. The High Republic introduces a new era in the Disney canon, set between 500 to 100 years prior to the films. 

Currently, The High Republic series consists of several novels, comics, and audio dramas, as well as official works originally created in other languages, including a Japanese manga series and a Chinese web novel. The Disney+ streaming series [[Star Wars: The Acolyte]] is also set in the High Republic era.

title: star_wars:_the_acolyte
body: The Acolyte, also known as Star Wars: The Acolyte, is an American science fiction television series created by Leslye Headland for the streaming service Disney+. It is part of the [[Star Wars]] franchise, set at the end of the High Republic era before the events of the Skywalker Saga, and follows a [[Jedi]] investigation into a series of crimes.

title: nintendo_switch_2
body:
[[Nintendo]]'s eighth video [[game console]], successor to [[Nintendo Switch]].

It was revealed on January 16, 2025 and released on June 5, 2025. 

Its [[Joy-Con 2]]s have a protrusion for clipping into the sides of the main body magnetically, rather than sliding onto the sides from the top like the original Switch.

title: hypnosis_mic:_alternative_rap_battle
body:
A mobile rhythm game based off the [[Hypnosis Mic]] franchise.

The protagonist is a [[protagonist_(hypnosis_mic:_alternative_rap_battle)|trainee DJ]] who is the apprentice of [[Doudantsutsuji Rokuro]]. After arriving at Chuohku to participate in the Alternative Rap Battle (the in-game analogue of the main series' Division Rap Battle), they become involved with four Division representatives, [[Buster Bros!!!]], [[MAD TRIGGER CREW]], [[Fling Posse]], and [[matenro_(hypnosis_mic)|Matenro]]. They also become acquainted with [[Dotsuitare Hompo]] and [[Bad Ass Temple]] in the Main Story's 2nd Season.

[b]Game-exclusive Characters[/b]
* [[protagonist_(hypnosis_mic:_alternative_rap_battle)|Protagonist]]

The story is original to the game and is not considered a part of the mainline Hypnosis Mic canon.

title: athena_cykes
body:
A new character in [[Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney - Dual Destinies]] who is playable in several cases. She is a rookie lawyer at [[Phoenix Wright]]'s agency and thus the junior of [[Apollo Justice]]. [[Juniper Woods]] is a childhood friend of her. Has the ability to discern emotions from the tone of a person's voice.

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[orange hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and [[sidelocks]], tied into a [[side ponytail]] and decorated with a [[blue ribbon|bl]][[blue hairband|ue]] [[hair ribbon|ribbon]] [[hairband]]. She also has [[blue eyes]].

She wears a [[single earring|single]] [[crescent earrings|crescent]] [[earrings|earring]], a [[necklace]] - Widget; an [[open jacket|open]] [[yellow jacket|yellow]] [[cropped jacket|cropped]] [[jacket]] with [[lapels]] and [[three-quarter sleeves]] that end in [[sleeve cuffs|cuffs]], a [[lapel pin]], a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[untucked shirt|untucked]] [[shirt]] with an [[open collar]], a [[blue necktie|blue]] [[necktie]], a [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black]] [[partially fingerless gloves|partially fingerless]] [[gloves|glove]], a [[yellow skirt|yellow]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt|mini]][[skirt]], [[black pantyhose|black]] [[pantyhose]], and [[white boots]].

[spoiler]Her mother was [[Metis Cykes]], who was murdered by a spy known as "The Phantom." [[Simon Blackquill]] was convicted of the murder instead, and Athena became a lawyer in order to overturn his sentence.[/spoiler]

[b]Japanese Name:[/b] Kizuki Kokone

title: living_doll_uniform
body:
The uniform worn by [[Shadows house]] Living Dolls. 

The female version consists of a [[black dress|dark]] [[blue dress]] with [[puffy sleeves]] [[three-quarter sleeves|coming up to the elbows]], a pair of [[blue socks|dark-blue socks]] and [[white boots]]. It's also attached with a [[white apron|white]] [[lace-trimmed apron]] when they're cleaning or doing chores and white lace ruffles collar when they do "face" duty. 

The male version consists of a [[white shirt|white button-up shirt]], [[blue pants|dark blue pants]], and it is also attached with a [[wing collar]], a [[green vest]], and a [[black bowtie]] when they’re cleaning or doing chores. When they are on "face" duty, they wears a [[blue shirt|dark blue shirt]] attached with a white lace ruffles collar over the standard outfit.

title: kirakishou
body:
[i]Snow Crystal[/i]

The seventh and final [[Rozen Maiden]] doll. She is both emotionally and physically unstable, being the only doll not given a body. She fights using [[white rose]] [[vines]]. She does not have a master, instead choosing to kidnap the others' masters.

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[blonde hair]] with [[two side up]] held with [[hair flower|roses]] and [[sidelocks]] and [[yellow eyes]] with a [[white rose]] [[flower over eye|over one eye]]. Her outfit is similar to [[Barasuishou]]'s [[lolita fashion]], consisting of a [[frilled shirt|frilled]] [[white shirt]] with [[wide sleeves|wide]] [[juliet sleeves]], a [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[white skirt]], and [[white boots|white]] [[lace-up boots|lace-up]] [[high heel boots|high-heel]] [[thigh boots]].

title: black_knight_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]]

Mysterious General from Daein's Army, he is known for the Jet-Black Armor he uses in combat that covers his body completely, which is said to be blessed by Tellius' Goddess, making it resistent to conventional weapons.

His weapon of choice is [[Alondite]], a legendary two-handed sword.

[spoiler]His true identity is [[Zelgius (Fire Emblem)|]], a Begnion general loyal to [[Sephiran (Fire Emblem)|]].[/spoiler]

title: head_only
body:
Character's head on its own, without a body. A neck and shoulders count as a body, if the shoulders are visible use [[cropped shoulders]] instead, if the neck is visible but shoulders are not, use [[cropped head]] instead.

Can be used when multiple heads or [[chibi]] ([[chibi inset|inset]]) are present.

[b]Do not use[/b] this tag for images where a (headless) body is present or as the  aftermath of decapitation, whether the body actually belongs to the head or not. In such cases, use [[severed head]] instead.

* !post #8940034

* !post #7751198: [[Cropped head]]. Visible neck and collarbone but no shoulders

title: juice_box
body:

title: carton
body:
Ambiguous tag. Try to use another tag if one exists.

* For a carton that starts off as a square box, but then forms a triangle at the top, use [[milk_carton]].
* For a small, hand-sized, typically rectangular container often accompanied by a [[drinking straw]], use [[juice_box]], or [[alcohol_carton]] if alcoholic.
* For any cubic or rectangular container used to hold something inside it, use [[box]] or, if applicable, [[cardboard_box]].

title: thigh_cuffs
body: A band typically of leather and/or metal that fits typically around the legs of a person. These bands are typically used to restrain the wearer by linking the cuffs together by chains or metal rods, and very frequently linked to the chastity belt. title: atelier_(series)

Most games stars a heroine just starting in the alchemy business when an event occurs and they must develop their skills to solve the problem. 

The Atelier Iris trilogy, Mana Khemia duology and Atelier Escha & Logy (from the Dusk trilogy) are the only games with male protagonists.

title: project_diva_(series)
body:
A series of rhythm action games published by [[SEGA]] featuring [[Hatsune Miku]] and her fellow Crypton [[Vocaloid]]s. The games were released on the [[PlayStation Portable]], [[Playstation Vita]], and [[Playstation 3]].

Gameplay consists of tapping and holding buttons corresponding to icons on the screen while listening to various Vocaloid songs. You can dress each Vocaloid in unique [[list_of_project_diva_modules|Modules]] (costumes) to dance in during each song, which you must unlock by clearing different conditions depending on the module. When not playing the rhythm games, you can view songs in PV mode, or interact with the Vocaloids themselves in the DIVA Room.

This tag may be used for images that reference Project DIVA in some way, but that don't depict modules from any of the games. Do not use the [[Vocaloid]] tag if the image does not include any Vocaloid characters in it.

title: cherry_blossoms
body:
Small [[flower]]s of any of several trees of the genus Prunus, especially the Japanese Cherry ([i]Prunus serrulata[/i], the suffix a Latin rendering of [i]sakura[/i]). Usually seen falling or scattered as [[petals]].

Cherry blossoms, especially the [[pink flower|pink]] ones of the [i]Prunus serrulata[/i], are a significant visual motif in Japanese culture; as their period of flowering that lasts little more than a week during the spring is thought to symbolically convey an awareness of the brilliant, yet impermanent nature of life. The term [i]mono no aware[/i] (物の哀れ, literally 'the pathos of things') was coined by 18th century scholar Motoori Norinaga to describe this concept as a theme found in classical Japanese literature, and associated it with the cherry blossom motif. 

The white-colored autumn and winter blossoms (冬桜, [i]fuyuzakura[/i]) of the higan cherry tree ([i]Prunus subhirtella autumnalis[/i]) are a notable variant, coming into bloom during those seasons. 

In anime and manga, besides straightforward symbolization of youth and verve, the [[flower symbol|symbol]] may be used to denote gentle and/or affectionate characters; though this usage can sometimes be ironic. [[Cherry tree]]s in anime art are almost always drawn in bloom, but the actual cherries don't grow until the blossoms are long gone.

Not to be confused with [[plum blossoms]]. Cherry petals have slits at the ends of the petals, while plum petal ends are round.

title: plum_blossoms
body:
The blossoms of plum trees, especially of the genus [i]Prunus mume[/i]. The petals are white, pink or red, and bloom in early spring. 

Distinguished from cherry blossoms in that cherry petals have slits at the ends of the petals. Plum petal ends on the other hand are round.

The plum blossom is the national flower of [[China]], and is an important cultural symbol in the country. Images depicting China more often feature plum blossoms than cherry blossoms.

title: donut
body:
A donut (also spelled "doughnut") is a small, fried pastry typically glazed with sugar, chocolate, or other frostings. It often contains sweet fillings such as cream, jelly, or custard.

The most common form is the ring-shaped donut, but the term also applies to round, filled donuts and other regional variants. Donuts are popular worldwide and appear frequently in food-related media and illustrations.

In American media, donuts are stereotypically associated with the [[police]], a trope that originated during the interwar period in the United States. Donuts were often the only food readily available during late-night or early morning shifts. To this day, donuts and coffee remain a classic breakfast combination in North American donut shops.

title: mauser_model_1889
body:
The [b]Mauser Model 1889[/b] is a [[belgium|Belgian]] [[bolt action]] [b][[rifle]][/b] fed with an internal 5-[[ammunition|round]] [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]] of 7.65×53mm Mauser.  The Model 1889 can be distinguished from other mauser rifles through being an cock-and-closing rifle and featured a single-piece solid wooden body running most of the length of the weapon, ending just aft of the muzzle. It contained two bands, and iron sights were fitted at the middle of the receiver top and at the muzzle like virtually all other rifles of the time. It was designed in 1889 to replace the Albini-Braendlin and Comblain single-shots.

title: p14_enfield
body:
The [b]Pattern 1914 Enfield[/b] or (The Rifle, .303 Pattern 1914 (or P14)) was a British [[bolt action]] [[rifle]] that was to replace the [[lee-enfield]] as standard-issued weapons for infantry, but was sidelined by its predecessor weapon, only produced in limited numbers during the First World War period. The [[weapon]] was developed as an hybrid rifle with a Mauser-like, cock-and-closing action and internal-box 5-round magazine, with an Enfield-style safety (on the opposite side of the receiver compared to the Enfield) and a cock-on-closing mechanism with a new and greatly improved sight. 

On the other hand, when the Americans entered the war in 1917, the Army realized that it couldn't get its hands on enough [[M1903 Springfield]]s to equip their infantry, so they had to acquire and produced their version of P'14 rifle, [[M1917 Enfield]] from private companies who was previously producing for the British, such as Remington, Winchester, and Eddystone, until enough M1903s was being sufficiently produced to equip the rest of the expeditionary force in the western front of the war.

h4. See also

* [[Lee-Enfield]]

title: choujikuu_seiki_orguss
body:
[i][b]Choujikuu Seiki Orguss[/b][/i] (超時空世紀オーガス), known in English as [i][b]The Super Dimension Century Orguss[/b][/i] (or more correctly as [i][b]The Hyperspace Century Orguss[/b][/i]) is a [[mecha]] science fiction TV series. It debuted on July 3, 1983 in Japan. The weekly series lasted 35 episodes. 

Orguss was the second part of [i]"The Super Dimension Trilogy"[/i] from [[Big West]], preceded by [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross|The Super Dimension Fortress Macross]] (1982) and then followed by [[Choujikuu Kidan Southern Cross|The Super Dimension Cavalry Southern Cross]] (1984). All these series were related in name only.

The first [[Orguss]] series had mechanical designs by [[Miyatake Kazutaka]] and character designs by [[Mikimoto Haruhiko]].

It is notable for being one of the first anime titles with an opening title song ([i]"Hyouryuu"[/i]), composed, arranged and sung by an American musician (the late [b]Casey Rankin[/b]).

Also of note is its main plot. While many mecha anime of the time and afterwards were [[space]] operas set mostly in an outer space environment Orguss dealt with the concepts of multiverses, alternate dimensions and/or different realities for the most part. 

This series is also one of the first sci-fi anime works to depict a [[space elevator]], along with [[uchuu_kuubo_blue_noah|Space Carrier Blue Noah]].

h4. Opening Theme - Hyouryuu

* https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ztw3EaoxPJM

title: lavalier_microphone
body:
A lavalier microphone or lavalier (also known as a lav, lapel mic, clip mic, body mic, collar mic, neck mic or personal mic) is a small [[microphone]] used for television, theater, and public speaking applications to allow hands-free operation. They are most commonly provided with small clips for attaching to collars, ties, or other clothing. The cord may be hidden by clothes and either run to a radio frequency transmitter kept in a pocket or clipped to a belt, or routed directly to the mixer or a recording device.

title: spring_onion
body:
A Japanese long onion, a variety of Welsh onion, sometimes called a Japanese leek in English due to their similar appearance. It is a vegetable often depicted as being shaped like a Y; a white twig with two green branches.

[[Hatsune Miku]] and [[Farfetch'd]] are known to carry this.

title: ishowspeed_trying_not_to_laugh_(meme)
body:
A [[meme]] referencing a clipped moment from one of [[IShowSpeed]]'s [[Fortnite]] streams on 31 December 2021, where he plays 1v1 wager battles against his fans. 

One of Speed's opponents, a seemingly financially-challenged teenager, starts to hysterically breakdown from his continuous defeats, crying about his struggling economic situation and how his mother is 'kinda homeless', which humors Speed from his delivery. However, he is called out by another player in-game for almost laughing, which forces Speed to suppress it, closing his eyes and making a smiling, tight-lipped expression.

h4. External links

* "Youtube: EARLY STREAM! (2:07:57)":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZIPCptw_Otg&t=7677s

title: judo_hold
body:
A [b]judo hold[/b], also known as a hold down and in Japanese as osaekomi-waza (抑え込み技, "pinning technique"), is a specific type of pinning hold technique found in [[judo]]. The original list of judo holding techniques was codified by Kano Jigoro and the Kodokan judo school.

The purpose of a hold in judo is to control and immobilize the opponent on their back for a specified period of time to achieve a score. This is contrasted with a [[submission hold]] or a [[joint lock]] where the goal is to force the opponent to submit or surrender. Judo holds may also be used in self-defense situations outside of judo practice or competition.

Judo holds have been incorporated into several different [[martial arts]] such as Brazilian jiu-jitsu, sambo and [[mixed martial arts]], and may still be tagged [[judo hold]].

h4. Related tags
* [[Arm triangle choke]]: type of choke that occurs when holding technique [i]Kata-gatame[/i] is applied correctly

h4. External links
* "List of judo holds on Wikipedia":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_judo_techniques#Osaekomi-waza_(抑込技):_pins_or_matholds]

title: submission_hold
body:
A [b]submission hold[/b] specifically refers to types of professional [[wrestling]] style moves used to immobilize an opponent causing them to surrender/submit.

For types of grappling techniques found in [[martial arts]] such as [[judo]] or jiu-jitsu, use [[judo hold]] or [[joint lock]] appropriately.

title: cagliostro_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
[i][[Granblue Fantasy]][/i] character.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. She wears [[black thighhighs]], [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]], a [[red skirt]] with [[vial|vials]] along the side of it, a [[tiara]]-like [[hairband]], and a [[cape]]. She is always holding a book.

She is actually over 1,000 years old, and is widely known in the Granblue universe as the person who basically invented alchemy. Her original male body was always of ill health and would've died in adolescence; to avoid such a fate, she learned how to use alchemy to create new bodies and transfer herself into them, thereby living indefinitely. This is how she wound up in her current female body, which she views as her "ideal" form.

Her nickname on the internet is "Uncle Cali" (カリおっさん, Cali-[i]ossan[/i]).

Note that, because her male form was never even seen in-series, Cagliostro's presence only warrants the [[genderswap_(mtf)]] tag if the image references it somehow. See topic #11614 for details.

h4.Official Alternate Costumes

* [[cagliostro_(summer)_(granblue_fantasy)|Summer Cagliostro]]

* [[cagliostro_(dark)_(granblue_fantasy)|Dark Cagliostro]]
* [[cagliostro (youthful_uniform) (granblue fantasy)|Youthful Uniform]]

title: scorpion
body:

They have eight legs and are easily recognized by the pair of grasping [[pincers]] and the narrow, segmented [[scorpion tail]], often carried in a characteristic forward curve over the back, ending with a venomous [[stinger]].

title: producer_(idolmaster_cinderella_girls_anime)
body:
The [[Producer (idolmaster)|]] that appears in the anime version of [[Idolmaster Cinderella Girls]].

A tall man with an imposing face, but actually a very quiet personality. He is often drawn with [[Shibuya Rin]] in fanarts.

He has a habit of [[hand on own neck|touching his neck]] when he is in trouble or distressed.

Voiced by [[Takeuchi Shunsuke]] (武内 駿輔), which is the base for his fan nickname TakeuchiP (武内P). At the time the anime came out, Takeuchi was only 17 years old, leading to jokes of the producer claiming he is 17 years old.

title: sakamata_chloe
body:
A [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] from [[hololive]]'s 6th generation "[[holoX]]". Designed by [[Parsley-F]].

Her general activities ended on January 26th, 2025, but she did not fully "graduate" and is still affiliated with Cover Corp, participating in future projects.

While canonically an [[orca girl]], she does not have enough orca-like features to be tagged as such on Danbooru.

She has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[grey hair]] with [[black hair|black]] [[streaked hair|streaks]], [[red eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. She also has [[multiple piercings|multiple]] [[spike piercing|spike]] and hoop [[ear piercing]] and an [[earclip]].

Her regular hairstyle with her default costume is [[wavy hair]] with [[double-parted bangs|double-parted]] [[center-flap bangs|center-flap]] [[braided bangs]], decorated with [[x hair ornament|crossing]] [[hairclip]]s. She also got an additional [[official alternate hairstyle]] for her default outfit consisting of [[long hair|long]] [[straight hair]] with sidelocks, a [[side braid]] and additional hairclips.

It is a [[gyaru]] type [[school uniform]], main elements being a [[red skirt]], [[white shirt]], [[pink jacket]], sometimes drawn as a cardigan.

Characters from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]].

A collective term used to refer to Nikkes that are mass-produced by the Big Three of the Ark, hence the name. Gameplay-wise, mass-produced Nikkes make up the R rarity of the Nikkes. There are numerous Mass-Produced Nikkes introduced in the game, notably the NPC one first introduced in the "Hightech Toy" event which is a generic NPC version introduced in later events.

The NPC version has [[brown hair]] and wears a [[visor]] which conceals their eyes along with [[medium breasts]]. They wear a [[green bodysuit]] with [[high heel boots]] and a pair of [[black gloves]]. They are often seen [[holding weapon|holding a gun]].

title: product_12_(nikke)
body:
A playable character in [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. One of the [[mass-produced Nikke]]s manufactured by Missilis Industry.

She has [[medium hair|medium]] [[brown hair]] and face covered by a [[visor]]. She wears a [[military uniform]] consisting of [[brown shirt]], [[body armor]], [[backpack]], and [[belt pouch]]. She is always seen [[holding gun|carrying]] a [[machine gun]].

Product 12 gain more prominence in the [[NieR:Automata]] crossover event "[i]OuteR: Automata[/i]," notably the four Product 12s with various nicknames all summoned by the Tyrant-class [[Rapture (nikke)|]] known as Gatekeeper via the D-Wave event:

* [b]P-12[/b] - a Product 12 seen accompanying [[A2 (nier:automata)|]]. Despite A2's reluctant trust to her due to being an outsider from an another world, P-12 still gives her best to help A2 in their folly.
* [b]C-1002[/b] - a Product 12 encountered by [[Counters (nikke)|]], she was known as "Lively Product 12." C-1002 took their code-names from a spy movie they watched alongside her company.
* [b]B-0006[/b] - a Product 12 known as "Cautious Product 12." She shows genuine concern over her fellow Product 12s, replicant or not. Wanting nothing more than peace and coexistence amongst all mass-produced models due to the D-Wave event, unable to bear the conflict amongst each other. [spoiler]She was eventually killed by 6000-D for this.[/spoiler]
* [b]6-000D[/b] - a Product 12 known as "Taciturn Product 12." She is actually the event's main antagonist.
other_names: プロダクト12(勝利の女神:NIKKE)

title: mogami_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese heavy cruiser [i]Mogami[/i]. Character design by [[Shibafu (glock23)|]], voiced by [[Suzaki Aya]].

She has [[short_hair|short]] [[black hair]] with [[swept bangs]], [[grey eyes]], and [[small breasts]]. Her default outfit is shared with her sister [i]Mikuma[/i]: a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[red shirt|red]] [[sailor shirt]] with a dark [[red sailor collar]], [[brown shorts]], [[black_socks|black]] [[kneehighs]], and black [[lace-up boots]].  

Her [[rigging]] consists of her real-life funnel and foremast to her back, four (or three at kai) 20.3 cm twin gun mounts, and a [[flight deck]] at kai form. She gains two [[radar]] sets at kai form as well. 

She is a frank, upbeat, energetic, and [[tomboy]]ish girl. Due to having collided three times in her historic service, she's commonly portrayed as quite clumsy, and too eager to watch where she's going. Collisions with her sister-ship [[Mikuma (Kancolle)|]] are most commonly portrayed. Because of her boyish looks, she is often portrayed as the target of rumors of being a boy, or outright portrayed as one.

h4. Appearance

title: pinne_(nikke)
body:
An NPC in [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]].

Name adopted by a mass-produced [[Product 23 (nikke)|]] in the Over Zone event. She would be the sole survivor of an entire force of mass-produced Nikkes assisting Goddess Squad in covering the Ark as its construction and final sealing were being completed. 

[spoilers]She would later become corrupted by Raptures and was subsequently executed by [[dorothy_(nikke)|Dorothy]]. This would be the beginning of Dorothy's downward spiral into severe depression, attempted suicide and later, hallucinations of Pinne.[/spoilers]

title: nut_king_call
body:
The [i][[Stand (JoJo)|Stand]][/i] of [[Higashikata Joshu]] in [[JoJolion]].

Nut King Call is a humanoid [[Stand (jojo)|]]. It has screws embedded in the sides of its head and its spindly arms. It has two shield-shaped eyes similar to a bug's and many nuts and bolts surrounding its neck resembling a ruff.

On its forehead rests a large V crest. Its face and arms are also textured with slight ridges. Its torso is covered in a tessellated [[triangle print]].

Namesake is the American jazz musician Nate King Cole.

title: mechanical_pussy

At a minimum, if the genital module has a visible border on the skin, separating it from the rest of the body.
Also suitable for single images of cybernetic or robotic female genitalia intended to be mounted as part of a [[robot]], [[android]] or [[cyborg]] body.
The tag is not used for an [[artificial vagina]], which is just a [[sex toy]].

body:

A short, fourteen years old girl from Melbourne, [[Australia]], she is the daughter of immigrants who came to Australia eighteen years ago. body:
[b]Tooth Fairy[/b] is a playable character in [[Reverse:1999]]. She works as a doctor of The Foundation, looking after young Arcanists, including [[vertin_(reverse:1999)|Vertin]] and [[sonetto_(reverse:1999)|Sonetto]]. By asking the patients to swallow a tooth fairy "or grounded up tooth fairy":[/posts/7210684], she can cure any of patient's toothache. Because of this, she was hated by toothfairies, and swore to make all of her teeth fall. Tooth Fairy (the person) prevent this by wearing braces. She is one of the main character in [b]A Nightmare in Green Lake[/b].

She is voiced by Alexandra Boyadjieff in English, and [[Uesaka Sumire]] in Japanese.

title: jessica_(reverse:1999)
body:
[b]Jessica[/b] is a playable character in [[Reverse:1999]]. She is an Arcane creature also known as [b]Changeling[/b] that can create illusions and command critters to do her bidding. She is one of the main characters in the event [b]A Nightmare at Green Lake[/b].

[spoiler]In the event, it is revealed that she was [[Blonney]]'s childhood friend. Fascinated with Blonney's horror stories, she turned herself into a hunan girl named [[Anne (Reverse:1999)|]] and lured people into the Green Lake, and "forced" them to act in. She was stopped by [[Vertin_(Reverse:1999)|Vertin]] and others who promised to take care of her and give her education in the human world.[/spoiler]

She was voiced by Lia Luz in English, and [[Waki Azumi]] in Japanese

The [b]Hyakkaryouran Resolution Council[/b] or Hyakkaryouran for short, is one of the many school clubs from [[Blue Archive]]. The Hyakkaryouran are the protagonists of Volume 5.

A club from Hyakkiyako Alliance Academy, the Hyakkaryouran have serve as the peacekeepers of Hyakkiyako since the Academy's founding. Hyakkaryouran members wear a sky-blue [[haori]] with white five-petaled flowers emblazoned across their sleeves and use Type 38 Arisaka Rifle.

Being a faction tag, this should only be used when at least four members of the group are present and equally in focus.

h4. Members

* [[Ayame (blue archive)|]]
* [[Nagusa (blue archive)|]]
* [[Kikyou (blue archive)|]]
* [[Renge (blue archive)|]]
* [[Yukari (blue archive)|]]
* [spoilers][[Kuzunoha (blue archive)|]] (Founder)[/spoilers]

title: knight
body:
A member of the [[warrior]] class during the Middle Ages in Europe commonly associated with chivalry and combat. Bred for their skills in horsemanship, swordsmanship and (in a fantasy millieu) magic. However, Danbooru is gracefully unprejudiced. Use this tag when you see a combination of at least three of the following:

* [[sword|Swords]] or [[lance|lances]]
* [[shield|Shields]]
* [[armor|Armor]] 
* [[horse|Horses]] or similar mounts, possibly clad in [[barding]]

If the character belongs to a Knight class from a game, then use this tag at your own discretion. If the character fits all of the above standards but is wearing clearly [[Japanese armor]] and carrying a [[katana]] rather than a European-style sword, use [[Samurai]] instead.

title: acid_graphics
body:
Graphic design style that blends the design elements of old school rave flyers with aspects of numerous other styles from the 1990s to the 2020s.

It often uses [[distortion]], [[grid background]]s, shapes inspired by [[cyber sigilism]], [[mixed media]] and [[3d]] elements, futuristic fonts, and repeated text.

title: i-401_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese submarine I-401, nicknamed "Shioi". Character design by [[Shibafu (glock23)|]], voiced by [[Ise Mariya]]. 

She has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[brown hair]] tied to a [[ponytail]], [[brown eyes]], [[tan]] skin, and is [[barefoot]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[blue one-piece swimsuit|blue]] [[school swimsuit]] with a [[name tag]], [[white shirt|white]] [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[side-tie shirt]] with an [[orange sailor collar]], and a [[hairclip]] patterned off her real-life fins. Her [[rigging]] consists of her torpedoes slung to her left side and her real-life conning tower, hangar, and [[aircraft catapult]] slung to her right. 

Her model is the Sen Toku-class aircraft-carrying submarine of the same name. The Sen Toku-class were once the largest submarines ever constructed and were originally meant for an attack on the Panama Canal. However, they were never used in any meaningful way as the few completed were only commissioned near the end of the war. The I-401 was sunk as a target off Pearl Harbor on May 31st 1946.

title: kidou_keisatsu_patlabor
body:
[i][b]Patlabor[/b][/i] (a portmanteau of "patrol" and "labor"), also known as [i][b]Mobile Police Patlabor[/b][/i] (機動警察パトレイバー), is an anime and manga [[science fiction]] franchise created in 1988 by "Headgear", a group consisting of manga artist [[Yuuki Masami]], director Oshii Mamoru, screenwriter Itō Kazunori, mecha designer [[Izubuchi Yutaka]], and character designer [[Takada Akemi]]. 

Patlabor is set in a near future [[Japan]], and it chronicles the exploits of a metropolitan [[police]] unit equipped with patrol [[mecha]]s called "Patlabors". 

The franchise includes a manga, a TV series, two OVA series, three feature-length movies (Patlabor The Movie, [[Kidou Keisatsu Patlabor 2 The Movie]], and WXIII: Patlabor the Movie 3), two light novel series, a short film compilation named [i][b]Minipato[/b][/i] (ミニパト) because of its [[chibi]] drawing style, a live-action series titled [[The Next Generation -Patlabor-]], and a reboot in the form of the [[Kidou Keisatsu Patlabor REBOOT]] pilot and [[Kidou Keisatsu Patlabor EZY]].

The original manga received the 36th Shogakukan Manga Award for shōnen in 1991.

title: garchomp
body:
A Dragon/Ground-type pseudo-Legendary [[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]], #0445 in the National Pokédex.

A bipedal, dark blue [[dragon]] with [[yellow eyes]], [[black sclera]], [[sharp teeth]], [[claws]], and [[spikes]] on its arms and legs. Notable for being the signature Pokémon of [[Cynthia (Pokemon)|]].

title: cartethyia_(wuthering_waves)
body:
Playable character in [[Wuthering Waves]].

The blessed maiden [[Fleurdelys (Wuthering Waves)|]], formerly known as Cartethyia before ascending as the chosen resonator of Rinascita's Sentinel, [[Imperator (Wuthering Waves)|]]. [spoilers]This story is later revealed to be a sham and a reverse of the real situation; Cartethyia is an uncorrupted fragment of [[Fleurdelys (Wuthering Waves)|]]'s soul embodying the desire to live.[/spoilers]

[[Tacet Mark (Wuthering Waves)|]] location: forehead

[i]If the image depicts an older version with a horn, tag as [[Fleurdelys (Wuthering Waves)|]] instead. If both are in frame, depending on the depiction, [[dual persona]] or [[transformation]] may apply.[/i]

Appears as a significantly aged up version of [[Cartethyia (Wuthering Waves)|]]. [spoilers]Later revealed to be a creation of and the resonator of the corrupted [[Imperator (Wuthering Waves)|]] after merging with the Rinascitan Threnodian Leviathan, as well as the original and complete form of [[Cartethyia (Wuthering Waves)|]].[/spoilers]

title: old_man's_wife_(guin_guin)
body:
An [[original|OC]] created by [[Guin Guin]] whomst appeared originally in the artist's [i][[kantai collection|Kancolle]][/i]-related works, the late wife of [[old man (guin guin)|old man Aldrino]] whom become the center of their ongoing [i][[Arknights]][/i] story as a stand-in for their world's [[Doctor (arknights)|]]. She had passed away long before the story begin.

Her real name has yet to be revealed since her debut story. She is sometimes shown in flashbacks as [[Kal'tsit (arknights)|]] often reminds Aldrino about her.

title: marjorie_(genshin_impact)
body:
An NPC from [[Genshin Impact]], she is the owner of the souvenier shop "With Wind Comes Glory" in Mondstadt. She is the daughter of [[Cyrus (genshin impact)|]], the Branch Master of the Adventurers' Guild in Mondstadt.

Marjorie has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and [[blue eyes]]. She wears a [[grey jacket|grey]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[double-breasted]] [[jacket]] overtop a [[blue dress]], [[brown gloves]], a [[brown pantyhose]] and a pair of [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]].

Voiced by [b]Nakatomi Mana[/b] in Japanese (same as [[Xianyun (genshin impact)|]]) and [[Erica Mendez]] in English (same as [[Kamisato Ayaka]]).

h4. See also

* [[List of Genshin Impact characters]]
